1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,502
[narrator] 
NOW THE STORY

2
00:00:02,502 --> 00:00:04,337
OF A WEALTHY FAMILY 
WHO LOST EVERYTHING...

3
00:00:04,337 --> 00:00:05,796
AND THE ONE SON 
WHO HAD NO CHOICE...

4
00:00:05,796 --> 00:00:07,132
BUT TO KEEP THEM ALL TOGETHER.

5
00:00:13,638 --> 00:00:15,640
IT'S ARRESTED DEVELOPMENT.

6
00:00:18,601 --> 00:00:20,603
[narrator] 
IT WAS MONDAY MORNING,

7
00:00:20,603 --> 00:00:22,897
AND MICHAEL BLUTH 
WAS NERVOUS ABOUT MEETING...

8
00:00:22,897 --> 00:00:25,441
WITH THE NEW PROSECUTOR 
OF HIS FATHER'S CRIMINAL CASE.

9
00:00:25,441 --> 00:00:27,735
- I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU'RE 
SO NERVOUS ABOUT, MICHAEL.

10
00:00:27,735 --> 00:00:29,987
IT'S A NEW PROSECUTOR. 
IT'S A WHOLE NEW BEGINNING,

11
00:00:29,987 --> 00:00:33,241
A NEW DAY, A NEW CASE, 
A WHOLE NEW SET OF LIES.

12
00:00:33,241 --> 00:00:34,450
- I'M NOT LYING ANYMORE, MOM.

13
00:00:34,450 --> 00:00:36,036
[narrator] 
MICHAEL WAS LYING.

14
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:38,163
HE FOUND HIS FUGITIVE FATHER 
EARLIER IN THE WEEK,

15
00:00:38,163 --> 00:00:40,206
AND HE WAS HIDING HIM 
IN THE ATTIC...

16
00:00:40,206 --> 00:00:41,832
WHERE GEORGE SR. 
WAS CURRENTLY WAITING

17
00:00:41,832 --> 00:00:43,293
FOR HIS BREAKFAST.

18
00:00:43,293 --> 00:00:45,378
- ABOUT THE BUSINESS, 
JUST FOR THE RECORD,

19
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:48,047
I WAS NOT INVOLVED WITH DAD 
BUILDING HOUSES IN IRAQ.

20
00:00:48,047 --> 00:00:49,840
THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT 
I'M GONNA TELL THEM.

21
00:00:49,840 --> 00:00:51,551
- IS THAT FOR LINDSAY?

22
00:00:51,551 --> 00:00:53,678
BECAUSE SHE'S NOT SCARED 
TO EAT IN FRONT OF ME ANYMORE.

23
00:00:53,678 --> 00:00:55,180
THOSE ARE 
THE WHITES ONLY, YES?

24
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:57,848
- THESE AREN'T FOR LINDSAY. 
THESE ARE MINE.

25
00:00:57,848 --> 00:00:59,809
- ANYWAY, I'M NOT LYING 
ANYMORE EITHER, MICHAEL.

26
00:00:59,809 --> 00:01:02,853
I'M BEING LIED...

27
00:01:02,853 --> 00:01:04,814
ON. 
- [gasps]

28
00:01:04,814 --> 00:01:06,899
- WOW. NOW MORE'S GONNA 
COME UP THAN GO DOWN.

29
00:01:09,902 --> 00:01:11,321
- I GOTTA GET OUTTA HERE.

30
00:01:11,321 --> 00:01:12,572
- HMM?

31
00:01:12,572 --> 00:01:14,240
- I CAN'T 
TAKE THIS ANYMORE.

32
00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:18,411
I MEAN, SHE'S JUST 
SO LOVING AND AFFECTIONATE.

33
00:01:18,411 --> 00:01:20,746
I-- I-- THIS IS NOT 
THE WOMAN I FELL IN LOVE WITH.

34
00:01:20,746 --> 00:01:22,915
- OSCAR, PLEASE. YOU CAN'T GO. 
YOU GOTTA STAY, OKAY?

35
00:01:22,915 --> 00:01:24,792
THIS IS THE NICEST SHE'S BEEN 
SINCE SHE FOUND OUT

36
00:01:24,792 --> 00:01:26,169
ROSA COULD BREAST-FEED BUSTER.

37
00:01:26,169 --> 00:01:27,837
- OH, BUSTER, DON'T EVEN 
BRING THAT UP.

38
00:01:27,837 --> 00:01:29,214
HE'S WELL INTO 
HIS ARMY TRAINING.

39
00:01:29,214 --> 00:01:31,090
[narrator] 
ACTUALLY, BUSTER HAD HIT A WALL

40
00:01:31,090 --> 00:01:32,383
IN HIS ARMY TRAINING.

41
00:01:32,383 --> 00:01:34,177
- I CAN'T DO IT!

42
00:01:34,177 --> 00:01:36,095
I CAN'T MAKE MY BED, 
AND I CAN'T DO THIS EITHER!

43
00:01:36,095 --> 00:01:38,264
AREN'T YOU SUPPOSED TO YELL 
AT ME AND CALL ME "HOMO"

44
00:01:38,264 --> 00:01:40,350
AND MOTIVATE ME OVER THIS WALL?

45
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:42,017
- WE CAN'T DO THAT ANYMORE. 
LAWSUIT.

46
00:01:42,017 --> 00:01:43,686
[narrator] 
IN FACT,

47
00:01:43,686 --> 00:01:45,938
IT WAS A RECENT RULING... 
PROSECUTED BY THE SAME MAN

48
00:01:45,938 --> 00:01:48,316
WHO MICHAEL WAS SOON 
TO MEET WITH.

49
00:01:48,316 --> 00:01:49,900
- IT'S GOING TO BE 
A LONG TIME BEFORE

50
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:51,736
SERGEANT WENDELL BAKER... 
CALLS SOMEONE

51
00:01:51,736 --> 00:01:53,904
"PRIVATE HOMO" AGAIN.

52
00:01:53,904 --> 00:01:56,031
- GOD WILLING, 
HE'LL FAIL BOOT CAMP.

53
00:01:56,031 --> 00:01:58,576
- WELL, WHY WOULDN'T HE? 
HE ALREADY FAILED DAY CAMP.

54
00:01:58,576 --> 00:02:01,204
HEY. 
- HI. HEY, DAD.

55
00:02:01,204 --> 00:02:02,413
YOU READY FOR THE PROSECUTOR?

56
00:02:02,413 --> 00:02:04,290
- HI. 
I HOPE SO.

57
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:06,667
HOW'D THAT MATH TEST WORK OUT? 
- OH, IT WAS OKAY, I GUESS.

58
00:02:06,667 --> 00:02:08,002
BUT-- I DON'T KNOW.

59
00:02:08,002 --> 00:02:09,337
IT WAS WEIRD. 
I STUDIED WITH ANN,

60
00:02:09,337 --> 00:02:10,963
BUT I STILL GOT A B-MINUS.

61
00:02:10,963 --> 00:02:12,590
- ANN GOT YOU A B-MINUS?

62
00:02:12,590 --> 00:02:15,718
- WELL, IT WASN'T ANN. 
SHE'S AN EXPERT IN MATH.

63
00:02:15,718 --> 00:02:18,053
ISN'T THAT CUTE? 
- IS IT?

64
00:02:18,053 --> 00:02:19,472
[narrator] 
MICHAEL FELT HIS SON

65
00:02:19,472 --> 00:02:20,806
WAS SETTING THE BAR TOO LOW...

66
00:02:20,806 --> 00:02:22,600
WITH HIS DATING STANDARDS.

67
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,560
- NO, IT WASN'T ANN'S FAULT.

68
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:28,814
I THINK I JUST ENDED UP THINKIN' 
ABOUT THE QUESTIONS TOO LONG.

69
00:02:28,814 --> 00:02:30,608
AND SO, BY THE TIME 
I PUT AN ANSWER DOWN,

70
00:02:30,608 --> 00:02:31,984
I WENT WITH, LIKE, 
MY FIFTH CHOICE

71
00:02:31,984 --> 00:02:33,611
OR SOMETHIN' LIKE THAT.

72
00:02:33,611 --> 00:02:35,821
- GEORGE MICHAEL, 
NEVER SETTLE FOR FIFTH CHOICE.

73
00:02:35,821 --> 00:02:37,365
SOMETHING BETTER 
IS GONNA COME ALONG.

74
00:02:37,365 --> 00:02:38,866
SHE JUST HAS TO.

75
00:02:38,866 --> 00:02:40,701
- I THINK MAYBE SITTING 
IN THE BACK OF THE CLASS

76
00:02:40,701 --> 00:02:42,245
WITH ANN IS A BAD IDEA.

77
00:02:42,245 --> 00:02:43,913
YOU KNOW, 
SHE'S JUST SO PRETTY.

78
00:02:43,913 --> 00:02:45,165
I GET DISTRACTED, 
I GUESS.

79
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:46,666
- DO YOU?

80
00:02:46,666 --> 00:02:48,918
- I WISH 
I COULD DRAW HER NOSE.

81
00:02:48,918 --> 00:02:51,421
- MAYBE IT'S YOUR EYES.

82
00:02:51,421 --> 00:02:53,298
MAYBE YOU NEED GLASSES... 
FOR YOUR GRADES.

83
00:02:53,298 --> 00:02:55,508
DIDN'T YOU SAY YOU HAD 
A HARD TIME READIN' THE BOARD...

84
00:02:55,508 --> 00:02:57,092
SITTIN' IN THE BACK ROW?

85
00:02:57,092 --> 00:02:58,844
- NO, I SAID I WAS 
IN THE BACK OF THE CLASSROOM.

86
00:02:58,844 --> 00:02:59,887
- THAT'S WHAT 
I MEAN. YEAH?

87
00:02:59,887 --> 00:03:01,096
- IT'S DIFFERENT. NO. NO.

88
00:03:01,096 --> 00:03:02,682
WELL, I DON'T KNOW. 
MAYBE.

89
00:03:02,682 --> 00:03:04,475
- NO, DEFINITELY. 
I'LL CALL THE EYE DOCTOR.

90
00:03:04,475 --> 00:03:06,060
- I GUESS.

91
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:07,853
- I'M GONNA SET YOU UP 
AN APPOINTMENT. OKAY?

92
00:03:07,853 --> 00:03:09,689
- HEY, GANG. 
- TOBIAS.

93
00:03:09,689 --> 00:03:11,649
- OH. OOH, I'M AFRAID 
I'LL HAVE TO TAKE THEM TO GO.

94
00:03:11,649 --> 00:03:13,025
I'M LATE FOR THE GYM.

95
00:03:13,025 --> 00:03:14,777
OH, AND ALSO, 
HERE'S A NUMBER...

96
00:03:14,777 --> 00:03:17,905
IN CASE THE BLUE MAN GROUP 
CALLS AND NEEDS AN UNDERSTUDY.

97
00:03:17,905 --> 00:03:20,575
I JUST FOUND OUT THAT MY 
CELLULAR TELEPHONE WAS A LEMON.

98
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:21,742
IT DIDN'T WORK.

99
00:03:21,742 --> 00:03:23,077
- [hoarse voice] 
NEITHER DO YOU.

100
00:03:23,077 --> 00:03:24,329
- [scoffs]

101
00:03:24,329 --> 00:03:25,996
- PRETTY BRAVE CARD 
FOR YOU TO PLAY.

102
00:03:25,996 --> 00:03:27,998
- I JUST CAN'T STAND IT. 
TOBIAS GETTING IN SHAPE...

103
00:03:27,998 --> 00:03:29,292
[door closing]

104
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:31,210
FOR A BUNCH 
OF SLUTTY GYM RATS.

105
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:33,671
- WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOUR VOICE? 
- NOTHING. I'VE BEEN GOING OUT.

106
00:03:33,671 --> 00:03:35,340
[narrator] 
LINDSAY HAD BEEN

107
00:03:35,340 --> 00:03:37,467
FREQUENTING SINGLES CLUBS, 
ALSO STILL HOPING TO MAKE

108
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:38,593
HER OPEN MARRIAGE WORK--

109
00:03:38,593 --> 00:03:39,802
- WHOO!

110
00:03:39,802 --> 00:03:41,304
[narrator] 
WHICH IT WON'T.

111
00:03:41,304 --> 00:03:44,098
- I DIDN'T CATCH THAT. 
- WHOO!

112
00:03:47,643 --> 00:03:50,145
I WONDER HOW MANY WOMEN 
HE'S SLEPT WITH, IF ANY.

113
00:03:50,145 --> 00:03:52,147
- LINDSAY, IT'S NOT 
A COMPETITION.

114
00:03:52,147 --> 00:03:54,442
- OF COURSE IT IS, MICHAEL. 
THAT'S WHY THEY CALL IT SCORING.

115
00:03:54,442 --> 00:03:56,151
- MAYBE IN THE '70s.

116
00:03:56,151 --> 00:03:58,153
- THAT MANY? WE'VE ONLY 
BEEN DOING THIS FOR A MONTH.

117
00:03:58,153 --> 00:03:59,614
- INSTEAD OF COMPETING 
WITH TOBIAS,

118
00:03:59,614 --> 00:04:00,990
WHY DON'T YOU TRY SPENDING...

119
00:04:00,990 --> 00:04:02,533
A LITTLE MORE TIME 
WITH YOUR DAUGHTER?

120
00:04:02,533 --> 00:04:03,576
- WHY? TOBIAS DOING THAT?

121
00:04:03,576 --> 00:04:04,952
[narrator] 
AT THAT MOMENT,

122
00:04:04,952 --> 00:04:06,621
LINDSAY'S DAUGHTER... 
[doorbell rings]

123
00:04:06,621 --> 00:04:08,205
WAS IN THE PROCESS 
OF WOOING HER OWN MAN.

124
00:04:08,205 --> 00:04:09,374
- WHO IS IT?

125
00:04:09,374 --> 00:04:10,625
- STEVE HOLT!

126
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:12,252
[narrator] 
MAEBY HAD EVEN STARTED

127
00:04:12,252 --> 00:04:13,753
ORDERING UNNECESSARY ITEMS...

128
00:04:13,753 --> 00:04:15,505
JUST TO HAVE MORE OCCASIONS 
TO SEE HIM.

129
00:04:15,505 --> 00:04:16,797
- UH, YOU ORDERED

130
00:04:16,797 --> 00:04:18,341
A "MEMORIES OF THANKSGIVING" 
BASKET?

131
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:19,842
- WOW, THAT LOOKS GREAT.

132
00:04:19,842 --> 00:04:21,927
- [hoarsely] 
MAEBY, WHO'S YOUR FRIEND?

133
00:04:21,927 --> 00:04:24,972
- IS THIS YOUR SISTER? 
- NO.

134
00:04:24,972 --> 00:04:27,182
BUT YOU JUST MADE MY DAY.

135
00:04:27,182 --> 00:04:29,852
- THANK YOU FOR THE BASKET. 
SEE YA.

136
00:04:31,604 --> 00:04:33,898
- [singsong] 
HE THINKS I'M CUTE.

137
00:04:33,898 --> 00:04:36,692
- HE'S 19. HE'S A SENIOR 
AT MY HIGH SCHOOL.

138
00:04:36,692 --> 00:04:39,320
[narrator] 
AND HAD BEEN FOR SEVERAL YEARS.

139
00:04:43,491 --> 00:04:45,285
- YOU KNOW WHAT?

140
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:47,912
I THINK I AM GONNA SPEND 
MORE TIME WITH MY DAUGHTER.

141
00:04:50,164 --> 00:04:53,000
- I CAN'T PROMISE YOU I WON'T 
TELL THE PROSECUTOR ABOUT THAT.

142
00:04:55,586 --> 00:04:57,338
- WHERE YOU BEEN?

143
00:04:57,338 --> 00:04:59,882
- ARE YOU WEARING MY 
DEAD WIFE'S MATERNITY CLOTHES?

144
00:04:59,882 --> 00:05:02,092
- YEAH. IT'S THE ONLY THING 
I COULD FIND.

145
00:05:02,092 --> 00:05:03,678
WHERE ARE THE EGGS?

146
00:05:03,678 --> 00:05:05,721
- DOCTOR SAYS THEY'RE BAD 
FOR THE BABY.

147
00:05:05,721 --> 00:05:07,473
- SO, YOU READY FOR 
THIS NEW PROSECUTOR?

148
00:05:07,473 --> 00:05:09,475
- I WAS UNTIL YOU CAME BACK.

149
00:05:09,475 --> 00:05:11,185
- YOU'RE NOT GONNA 
TURN ME IN, ARE YOU?

150
00:05:11,185 --> 00:05:12,603
BECAUSE I HAD NO IDEA

151
00:05:12,603 --> 00:05:14,772
THERE WERE SANCTIONS 
AGAINST, UH, IRAQ.

152
00:05:14,772 --> 00:05:16,231
YOU KNOW, 
TH-THEY SENT ME OVER THERE.

153
00:05:16,231 --> 00:05:17,900
THEY SAID, "GO BUILD."

154
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:20,194
UH-- UH, DO I LOOK LIKE 
A CRIMINAL MASTERMIND TO YOU?

155
00:05:20,194 --> 00:05:21,696
HOW DO YOU GET THIS HAM OPEN?

156
00:05:21,696 --> 00:05:23,072
I CAN'T-- I CAN'T GET 
THIS HAM OPEN.

157
00:05:23,072 --> 00:05:24,365
- I'M NOT GONNA TURN YOU IN.

158
00:05:24,365 --> 00:05:25,616
BUT YOU HAVE PUT ME 
IN A POSITION

159
00:05:25,616 --> 00:05:27,159
WHERE I'M GONNA HAVE TO LIE.

160
00:05:27,159 --> 00:05:28,953
WHY DID YOU COME BACK HERE 
IN THE FIRST PLACE?

161
00:05:28,953 --> 00:05:30,580
- OH, NO REASON.

162
00:05:30,580 --> 00:05:32,457
YOUR MOTHER HAPPENS TO BE 
SHTUPPING MY BROTHER,

163
00:05:32,457 --> 00:05:34,249
THAT'S ALL.

164
00:05:34,249 --> 00:05:36,168
I'M ONLY HERE TO FIND OUT 
IF I HAVE A SHOT WITH HER.

165
00:05:36,168 --> 00:05:37,628
IF SHE'S REALLY IN LOVE 
WITH OSCAR--

166
00:05:37,628 --> 00:05:39,129
I DON'T KNOW-- 
TO HELL WITH HER.

167
00:05:39,129 --> 00:05:40,548
I'LL JUST-- 
I'LL JUST LEAVE.

168
00:05:41,924 --> 00:05:43,426
I'LL NEVER COME BACK.

169
00:05:43,426 --> 00:05:45,470
- GREAT. SHE'S REALLY 
IN LOVE WITH HIM.

170
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:48,389
- THAT'S VERY FUNNY. 
I NEED YOU TO FIND OUT, OKAY?

171
00:05:48,389 --> 00:05:50,516
'CAUSE EVER SINCE 
I-- I HEARD ABOUT THIS--

172
00:05:50,516 --> 00:05:52,685
[breathes deeply] 
I CAN'T SLEEP.

173
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:55,104
I CAN'T-- I CAN'T EAT.

174
00:05:55,104 --> 00:05:58,858
OH. LOOK, IT JUST PEELS OFF. 
ISN'T THAT CLEVER?

175
00:05:58,858 --> 00:06:00,735
[narrator] 
LATER THAT DAY, GEORGE MICHAEL

176
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:02,737
WAS HAVING HIS EYE EXAM... 
AND FINDING IT TO BE

177
00:06:02,737 --> 00:06:05,615
JUST AS DIFFICULT 
AS HIS MATH EXAM.

178
00:06:05,615 --> 00:06:08,075
- ONE OR TWO? 
- TWO. NO. NO, ONE.

179
00:06:08,075 --> 00:06:12,997
- OKAY. TWO OR THREE? 
- THREE.

180
00:06:12,997 --> 00:06:14,957
UH, UNLESS THREE IS 
TOO MUCH OF AN IMPROVEMENT.

181
00:06:14,957 --> 00:06:17,292
I'M SORRY, IS ONE-- IS ONE 
IN THE MIX STILL?

182
00:06:17,292 --> 00:06:18,586
[narrator] 
AND MICHAEL MET

183
00:06:18,586 --> 00:06:20,212
WITH THE NEW PROSECUTOR, 
WAYNE JARVIS.

184
00:06:20,212 --> 00:06:22,089
- I'M SORRY.

185
00:06:22,089 --> 00:06:24,383
I DON'T UNDERSTAND HOW THIS 
IS NOT A CONFLICT OF INTEREST.

186
00:06:24,383 --> 00:06:26,719
YOU ALMOST REPRESENTED US, 
AND NOW YOU'RE THE PROSECUTOR.

187
00:06:26,719 --> 00:06:28,178
- THE PATRIOT ACT. 
READ IT.

188
00:06:28,178 --> 00:06:29,764
- I-I'M NOT EVEN 
THE PRESIDENT ANYMORE.

189
00:06:29,764 --> 00:06:31,348
MY BROTHER GOB IS.

190
00:06:31,348 --> 00:06:33,308
- I SPOKE WITH GOB. 
HE APPEARS TO KNOW NOTHING.

191
00:06:33,308 --> 00:06:35,603
- YEAH, THAT'S NOT AN ACT. 
HE TWICE TRIED TO MICROWAVE...

192
00:06:35,603 --> 00:06:37,730
A DING DONG 
WHILE IT WAS STILL IN ITS FOIL.

193
00:06:37,730 --> 00:06:39,524
TWICE. 
- TWICE?

194
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:40,566
- TWO TIMES.

195
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:41,651
[narrator] 
IN FACT,

196
00:06:41,651 --> 00:06:43,360
GOB HAD BEEN GRILLED EARLIER.

197
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:45,195
- I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING 
ABOUT THE BUSINESS!

198
00:06:45,195 --> 00:06:46,739
- WE'RE GONNA GET YOU, BLUTH.

199
00:06:46,739 --> 00:06:48,783
WE'LL GIVE YOU 
A FEW MINUTES TO THINK

200
00:06:48,783 --> 00:06:49,909
ABOUT WHAT YOU WANT TO DO.

201
00:06:52,495 --> 00:06:54,955
HE KNOWS LESS THAN ANYONE 
WE HAVE EVER QUESTIONED.

202
00:06:54,955 --> 00:06:56,206
[narrator] 
GOB KNEW TOO LITTLE

203
00:06:56,206 --> 00:06:57,958
TO KNOW THAT, HOWEVER,

204
00:06:57,958 --> 00:07:01,128
AND HIS CONFIDENCE 
HAD NEVER BEEN MORE SHAKEN.

205
00:07:01,128 --> 00:07:02,880
AND JUST WHEN HE THOUGHT 
HE COULDN'T HANDLE

206
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:04,507
ANOTHER EMBARRASSMENT--

207
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:06,551
- YOU'RE FREE TO GO.

208
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:08,928
THINGS COULD GET VERY MESSY 
FOR YOU, MICHAEL, UNLESS YOU

209
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:10,596
HAVE SOMETHING TO BARGAIN WITH,

210
00:07:10,596 --> 00:07:12,682
LIKE, SAY, A FUGITIVE.

211
00:07:12,682 --> 00:07:14,391
- I DON'T KNOW 
WHERE TO FIND SUCH A THING.

212
00:07:14,391 --> 00:07:15,893
- LOOK HARDER.

213
00:07:15,893 --> 00:07:17,478
THERE MIGHT BE 
SOMETHING IN IT FOR YOU.

214
00:07:17,478 --> 00:07:19,146
- SOMETHING TO GET 
ME OFF THE HOOK?

215
00:07:19,146 --> 00:07:21,816
- IF YOU COULD FIND 
A CERTAIN SOMEONE.

216
00:07:21,816 --> 00:07:25,486
- CAN I HAVE A MOMENT ALONE 
WITH MY CLIENT, PLEASE?

217
00:07:25,486 --> 00:07:29,073
DID YOU FOLLOW ANY OF THAT?

218
00:07:29,073 --> 00:07:31,576
- YEAH. HE'S HINTING THAT 
HE'S GONNA GRANT ME IMMUNITY,

219
00:07:31,576 --> 00:07:33,869
BUT ONLY ON THE CONDITION 
THAT I TURN IN MY FATHER.

220
00:07:33,869 --> 00:07:36,831
- YOU KNOW WHERE YOUR FATHER IS? 
