00:15:41,773 --> 00:15:44,401
IN THE PATRIOT ACT, THE PHOTOS 
HAD MADE THE ROUNDS...

445
00:15:44,401 --> 00:15:47,529
THROUGH SEVERAL BRANCHES 
OF GOVERNMENT...

446
00:15:47,529 --> 00:15:49,781
AND ULTIMATELY 
TO THE U.S. ARMY ITSELF.

447
00:15:49,781 --> 00:15:52,034
- I JUST CAME BACK TO TELL YOU. 
I CAN'T DO THAT WALL.

448
00:15:52,034 --> 00:15:54,328
- THERE'S NO TIME FOR THAT. 
WE'RE SHIPPING OUT WITHOUT YOU.

449
00:15:54,328 --> 00:15:56,538
- WHAT? 
- DIDN'T YOU SEE?

450
00:15:56,538 --> 00:15:58,290
- PICK IT UP. PICK IT UP.

451
00:15:58,290 --> 00:16:01,293
- WEAPONS OF MASS DESTRUCTION?

452
00:16:01,293 --> 00:16:03,587
- THOSE BASTARDS. 
- I DID NOT SAY THAT.

453
00:16:03,587 --> 00:16:04,964
- ARE YOU GONNA LET THAT SLIDE?

454
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:07,591
ARE YOU GONNA 
ALLOW YOUR CHILDREN,

455
00:16:07,591 --> 00:16:09,676
AND YOUR CHILDREN'S CHILDREN,

456
00:16:09,676 --> 00:16:11,886
AND ANY CHILDREN 
THAT I MIGHT HAVE OUT THERE...

457
00:16:11,886 --> 00:16:14,639
TO LIVE IN FEAR 
FOR THE REST OF THEIR LIVES?

458
00:16:14,639 --> 00:16:17,559
CLIMB THAT WALL, HOMO!

459
00:16:17,559 --> 00:16:19,311
- CLIMB IT.

460
00:16:19,311 --> 00:16:20,937
[narrator] 
AND JUST AS THE MEN THOUGHT

461
00:16:20,937 --> 00:16:22,564
THE DAY COULD 
GET NO MORE SURPRISING,

462
00:16:22,564 --> 00:16:24,608
[yelling] 
IT DID.

463
00:16:24,608 --> 00:16:26,068
- OHH! OOH! 
[thuds]

464
00:16:26,068 --> 00:16:27,652
[whimpering]

465
00:16:27,652 --> 00:16:29,488
- WHEN YOU DO THIS 
WITHOUT GETTING PUNCHED,

466
00:16:29,488 --> 00:16:30,990
YOU'LL HAVE MORE FUN.

467
00:16:30,990 --> 00:16:33,325
- OH, HEY, GEORGE MICHAEL. 
- OH, HI.

468
00:16:33,325 --> 00:16:35,410
- THEY FOUND W.M.D.'s IN IRAQ, 
SO WE GOT A HALF DAY.

469
00:16:35,410 --> 00:16:38,497
- COOL. SO I GOT 
A "C" ON MY MATH TEST.

470
00:16:38,497 --> 00:16:40,832
NOT ANTICIPATING 
A GOOD REACTION ON THAT.

471
00:16:40,832 --> 00:16:42,251
- WELL, THE "B" GOT YOU GLASSES.

472
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:44,461
MAYBE THIS TIME 
YOU'LL GET A NECK BRACE.

473
00:16:44,461 --> 00:16:47,839
ANYWAYS, HAVE YOU SEEN MY MOM?

474
00:16:47,839 --> 00:16:49,299
- SEEMS POSSIBLE.

475
00:16:49,299 --> 00:16:50,717
- SHE'S ON HER WAY 
TO MEET STEVE HOLT.

476
00:16:50,717 --> 00:16:52,636
- I THOUGHT YOU LIKED HIM.

477
00:16:52,636 --> 00:16:54,763
- I DO. I'M CRAZY ABOUT HIM. 
BUT HE'S OBSESSED WITH HER.

478
00:16:54,763 --> 00:16:56,681
THAT'S ALL HE WANTS 
TO TALK ABOUT.

479
00:16:56,681 --> 00:16:58,100
[narrator] 
LINDSAY FELT BAD.

480
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,768
PERHAPS SHE HAD 
HURT HER DAUGHTER...

481
00:16:59,768 --> 00:17:01,020
BY PUTTING HERSELF FIRST.

482
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,729
BUT SHE WOULD HAVE FELT WORSE

483
00:17:02,729 --> 00:17:04,564
IF SHE'D REMAINED 
EVEN A MOMENT LONGER.

484
00:17:04,564 --> 00:17:06,816
- BUT IT'S ONLY BECAUSE 
HE THINKS SHE'S GOT A PENIS.

485
00:17:06,816 --> 00:17:08,443
OH, I TOLD HIM 
SHE WAS A TRANNY.

486
00:17:08,443 --> 00:17:09,861
[narrator] 
MEANWHILE, MICHAEL WAS

487
00:17:09,861 --> 00:17:11,488
STILL UP IN THE ATTIC.

488
00:17:11,488 --> 00:17:13,407
- DAD, WHAT'S GOIN' ON? 
SOMEBODY COULD SEE YOU.

489
00:17:13,407 --> 00:17:15,075
- WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE, MIKE?

490
00:17:15,075 --> 00:17:16,993
YOU'RE TURNING ME IN, 
AREN'T YOU?

491
00:17:16,993 --> 00:17:19,163
- THEY SAY YOU'RE INVOLVED 
IN SOMETHING REAL BIG, DAD.

492
00:17:19,163 --> 00:17:20,747
THEY'VE GOT PHOTOS.

493
00:17:20,747 --> 00:17:23,042
- NOT TRUE. BUT GO. 
KNOCK YOURSELF OUT. TURN ME IN.

494
00:17:23,042 --> 00:17:25,710
I WENT AND I SAW FOR MYSELF.

495
00:17:25,710 --> 00:17:27,671
SHE'S IN LOVE WITH HIM.

496
00:17:29,756 --> 00:17:31,466
- THEN WHY DID YOU COME BACK?

497
00:17:31,466 --> 00:17:33,427
WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST 
LEAVE FOREVER LIKE YOU SAID?

498
00:17:33,427 --> 00:17:34,969
- AND GO WHERE?

499
00:17:34,969 --> 00:17:36,346
[sighs]

500
00:17:36,346 --> 00:17:38,432
MAKE A DEAL 
FOR YOURSELF, MIKE.

501
00:17:38,432 --> 00:17:40,559
I GOT NO LOVE 
IN MY LIFE ANYMORE.

502
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:41,893
[narrator] 
AND MICHAEL REALIZED

503
00:17:41,893 --> 00:17:43,812
FOR THE FIRST TIME...

504
00:17:43,812 --> 00:17:46,148
THAT HIS FATHER WAS CAPABLE 
OF HAVING HIS HEART BROKEN.

505
00:17:46,148 --> 00:17:47,607
LATER THAT DAY,

506
00:17:47,607 --> 00:17:49,526
MICHAEL HAD HIS MEETING 
WITH THE PROSECUTOR.

507
00:17:49,526 --> 00:17:50,944
- SO, WHERE THE HELL IS HE?

508
00:17:50,944 --> 00:17:52,362
COME ON, BLUTH. 
WHAT'S IT GONNA BE?

509
00:17:52,362 --> 00:17:54,989
YOUR FATHER OR YOUR FREEDOM?

510
00:17:54,989 --> 00:17:56,325
[narrator] 
AND MICHAEL HAD TO DO

511
00:17:56,325 --> 00:17:57,992
THE RIGHT THING.

512
00:17:57,992 --> 00:18:00,079
- I DON'T KNOW 
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM.

513
00:18:02,539 --> 00:18:04,333
- MICHAEL, WHEN WE STARTED 
TALKING TO YOU,

514
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:05,667
WE DIDN'T HAVE ANYTHING.

515
00:18:05,667 --> 00:18:08,545
BUT NOW... WE GOT SOMETHING.

516
00:18:08,545 --> 00:18:10,046
AND YOU'RE GONNA 
DO TIME FOR IT.

517
00:18:10,046 --> 00:18:11,506
- THOSE ARE THE PICTURES?

518
00:18:11,506 --> 00:18:14,050
- THEY'RE ALL OVER THE NEWS.

519
00:18:14,050 --> 00:18:16,428
- THOSE ARE BALLS. 
- WHAT?

520
00:18:16,428 --> 00:18:17,887
[narrator] 
BARRY WAS RIGHT.

521
00:18:17,887 --> 00:18:19,973
TOBIAS HAD INADVERTENTLY 
PHOTOGRAPHED HIMSELF...

522
00:18:19,973 --> 00:18:21,933
WHILE LEARNING TO USE 
HIS CAMERA PHONE.

523
00:18:21,933 --> 00:18:25,270
- SEE, UH, THIS CLOSE, 
THEY ALWAYS LOOK LIKE LANDSCAPE.

524
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:28,565
NOPE, YOU'RE LOOKIN' AT BALLS.

525
00:18:28,565 --> 00:18:30,150
[narrator] 
SOON, FORENSIC SCIENTISTS

526
00:18:30,150 --> 00:18:31,568
CONFIRMED THIS.

527
00:18:31,568 --> 00:18:33,403
AND FOR THE SECOND TIME 
IN TWO DAYS,

528
00:18:33,403 --> 00:18:35,447
THE INFORMATION-SHARING NETWORK 
PUT INTO PLACE

529
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:36,865
BY THE PATRIOT ACT...

530
00:18:36,865 --> 00:18:38,908
WAS PUT TO USE.

531
00:18:38,908 --> 00:18:41,786
- THEY'RE BALLS?

532
00:18:41,786 --> 00:18:43,788
- WE'RE LOOKING AT BALLS. 
LET'S TURN IT AROUND.

533
00:18:43,788 --> 00:18:45,332
- COPY ON BALLS. 
WE'RE TURNING.

534
00:18:45,332 --> 00:18:46,958
[narrator] 
AND EVENTUALLY, THE NEWS

535
00:18:46,958 --> 00:18:48,793
TRAVELED BACK TO THE SOURCE.

536
00:18:48,793 --> 00:18:51,921
- WE GOT ONE WRONG, 
AND WE DO APOLOGIZE.

537
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:56,926
- I'M ON TV.

538
00:18:56,926 --> 00:18:58,553
[narrator] 
AND MICHAEL RETURNED HOME

539
00:18:58,553 --> 00:18:59,596
A FREE MAN.

540
00:18:59,596 --> 00:19:01,265
- YOU GOT THE GLASSES.

541
00:19:01,265 --> 00:19:02,974
NOW YOU'LL DO BETTER 
ON THOSE MATH EXAMS.

542
00:19:02,974 --> 00:19:04,518
- I THINK I BLEW 
THE EYE EXAM TOO.

543
00:19:04,518 --> 00:19:06,645
EVERY TIME I TAKE THESE OFF, 
I FEEL BETTER.

544
00:19:06,645 --> 00:19:09,398
- LET ME SEE 'EM.

545
00:19:09,398 --> 00:19:10,982
- I'VE SEEN THIS BEFORE.

546
00:19:10,982 --> 00:19:13,026
[narrator] 
FOR A WHILE, GEORGE MICHAEL...

547
00:19:13,026 --> 00:19:15,362
HAD SHARED A ROOM 
WITH HIS UNCLE TOBIAS.

548
00:19:15,362 --> 00:19:17,030
- OH, TH-THERE'S A LADDER.

549
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:20,492
- [groaning] 
I DON'T NEED IT.

550
00:19:20,492 --> 00:19:24,204
- YEAH, I DON'T THINK 
YOU NEED GLASSES, SON.

551
00:19:24,204 --> 00:19:27,499
- WELL, IF THE COPS ARE WAITING, 
I'M READY TO GO.

552
00:19:27,499 --> 00:19:29,543
I GOT NOTHIN' 
SINCE YOUR MOTHER DESERTED ME.

553
00:19:29,543 --> 00:19:31,336
- YOU KNOW, 
YOU-- YOU DESERTED HER, DAD.

554
00:19:31,336 --> 00:19:33,547
YOU KNOW, YOU ESCAPED, 
AND THEN YOU FAKED YOUR DEATH.

555
00:19:33,547 --> 00:19:36,007
I'M NOT SO SURE SHE SEES YOU 
AS THAT RELIABLE.

556
00:19:36,007 --> 00:19:38,385
BUT, LISTEN, 
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,

557
00:19:38,385 --> 00:19:40,345
I DID NOT TURN YOU IN.

558
00:19:42,138 --> 00:19:44,308
- YOU DIDN'T? 
- NO.

559
00:19:44,308 --> 00:19:45,850
AND I DON'T KNOW 
WHETHER IT'S JUST

560
00:19:45,850 --> 00:19:47,602
TRACY'S MATERNITY CLOTHES,

561
00:19:47,602 --> 00:19:50,189
BUT IT'S VERY NICE TO SEE 
A SOFTER SIDE OF YOU.

562
00:19:50,189 --> 00:19:51,773
ALTHOUGH I'M SORRY

563
00:19:51,773 --> 00:19:54,150
THAT YOU FEEL YOU HAVE 
NO LOVE IN YOUR LIFE.

564
00:19:54,150 --> 00:19:56,528
- WELL, I DON'T-- 
I DON'T FEEL THAT WAY ANYMORE.

565
00:19:59,072 --> 00:20:01,115
THANKS.

566
00:20:01,115 --> 00:20:03,910
BEEN A LONG TIME 
SINCE SOMEONE STOOD UP FOR ME.

567
00:20:07,038 --> 00:20:08,623
- FOUND HER PERFUME, HUH?

568
00:20:08,623 --> 00:20:09,958
- JUST A LITTLE 
LEFT IN THE BOTTLE.

569
00:20:09,958 --> 00:20:11,125
- WELL, THAT WAS 
THE END OF IT.

570
00:20:11,125 --> 00:20:12,502
- YEAH.

571
00:20:12,502 --> 00:20:14,338
- IT'S NICE ON YOU. 
- THANK YOU.

572
00:20:14,338 --> 00:20:15,505
[narrator] 
ON THE NEXT

573
00:20:15,505 --> 00:20:17,216
ARRESTED DEVELOPMENT.

574
00:20:17,216 --> 00:20:20,427
OSCAR RETURNS TO FIND 
A NOW-DISTANT LUCILLE.

575
00:20:20,427 --> 00:20:23,597
- I'M BACK. 
BUT JUST FOR NOW.

576
00:20:23,597 --> 00:20:25,724
'CAUSE YOU GET 
ON MY CASE-- SHOO--

577
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:28,352
- I AM OUT OF HERE. 
- THEN GO. WHO NEEDS YOU?

578
00:20:28,352 --> 00:20:30,354
[narrator] 
WHICH WAS WHAT

579
00:20:30,354 --> 00:20:32,105
ATTRACTED HIM TO HER... 
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

580
00:20:32,105 --> 00:20:33,398
- GOD, I MISSED YOU.

581
00:20:33,398 --> 00:20:34,774
[narrator] 
LINDSAY RECONCILS

582
00:20:34,774 --> 00:20:36,235
WITH HER DAUGHTER.

583
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:37,652
- HEY, MOM. 
I GOT YOU SOMETHIN'.

584
00:20:37,652 --> 00:20:38,695
- THAT IS SO SWEET.

585
00:20:38,695 --> 00:20:40,196
YOU KNOW WHAT?

586
00:20:40,196 --> 00:20:41,990
I WAS HOPING WE COULD 
GO TO DINNER TONIGHT.

587
00:20:41,990 --> 00:20:44,200
- OH, I THOUGHT YOU WERE GONNA 
GO SEE STEVE HOLT AT SCHOOL.

588
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:46,202
- NO, I JUST WANTED 
TO CHECK HIM OUT...

589
00:20:46,202 --> 00:20:49,038
AND MAKE SURE HE'S 
GOOD ENOUGH FOR MY DAUGHTER.

590
00:20:49,038 --> 00:20:51,500
IS IT-- 
- IT'S A "SHEH-MA-LEE."

591
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:53,543
- IT'S GORGEOUS.

592
00:20:53,543 --> 00:20:55,712
I'M WEARING IT TO DINNER.

593
00:20:55,712 --> 00:20:57,297
[narrator] 
TOBIAS, TRAUMATIZED BY

594
00:20:57,297 --> 00:20:58,590
THE PUBLIC EXPOSURE,

595
00:20:58,590 --> 00:21:00,884
RETURNS TO 
AN UNFORTUNATE QUIRK.

596
00:21:00,884 --> 00:21:02,844
- THANK GOD! 
MY CUTOFFS.

597
00:21:07,766 --> 00:21:09,768
- THERE WERE 
CUTOFFS UP HERE?
